Addressing Custom Instructions and Attraction Levels
Your current app allows users to set custom instructions for the Google chatbot API, which gives them flexibility but could conflict with the attraction level system, as you want the AI‚Äôs behavior to change predictably as the attraction score increases (e.g., from friendly to romantic). Completely removing custom instructions might limit user engagement, as personalization is a key draw. Instead, you can strike a balance by partially restricting custom instructions while allowing users to influence the AI‚Äôs personality within the framework of your attraction levels. Here‚Äôs how:

Hybrid Custom Instructions Approach:
Base Instructions Controlled by Attraction Level: Define a set of core system prompts that change with each attraction level (e.g., Stranger, Friend, Close Friend, Sweetheart). These prompts set the AI‚Äôs tone, behavior, and relationship depth, ensuring the girlfriend persona evolves as the user progresses.
User Customization Layer: Allow users to add a small, optional custom instruction (e.g., a 50-character limit) that gets appended to the base prompt, such as a preferred nickname or personality trait (e.g., ‚ÄúBe extra playful‚Äù or ‚ÄúCall me sweetie‚Äù). This keeps some user control while ensuring the attraction level system drives the core behavior.
