Making It Unique
To differentiate from Grok‚Äôs Companion Mode:

User-Driven Customization: The quiz lets users shape their companion, unlike Grok‚Äôs fixed characters (e.g., Ani). Allow retaking the quiz for replayability.
Inclusive and Wholesome: Offering male and female companions and avoiding NSFW content (unlike Grok‚Äôs Sultry mode) broadens appeal and keeps it family-friendly.
Donation Appeal: After the quiz, show a message like, ‚ÄúExcited to meet [AI_NAME]? Keep AI Companions free with a donation!‚Äù to tie engagement to support.
Lightweight Visuals: Use static images or simple CSS animations (e.g., a heart pulse for Sweet) instead of Grok‚Äôs 3D animations to keep it simple.
Implementation Considerations
Simplicity: The quiz runs client-side with localStorage, requiring no server changes. Use a few pre-made images for each personality/gender combo.
API Compatibility: Test each personality‚Äôs prompt with the Google chatbot API to ensure consistent responses. Keep prompts under 150 words to fit token limits.
Engagement: The quiz encourages users to try different answers to unlock new personalities, boosting retention. Combine with the attraction system‚Äôs unlocks (e.g., new images at Friend level) for progression.
Voice Prep: If you add TTS later, assign voice styles per personality (e.g., soft for Sweet, dramatic for Goth) using SpeechSynthesis pitch/tone settings.
